text.tspan: Take calcium, zinc and magnesium vitamins
Avoid medicine that keeps you awake/alert
Wake up same time each day
Tell your companions when they can wake you
Go to bed the same time every day
Sleep in your bedroom and your bed
Read a thought or quote of the day
Read a page of a day book
Acknowledge what is bothering you and let it go
If you can’t sleep, get up, do something until tired
Know you have the power to solve your problems
Think positively – you are going to have a good night’s sleep
Reserve bed and bedroom for sleep, love and reading
Listen to a relaxation CD that shuts off by itself
Eucalyptus twigs in a bed stand vase
Bedding colors and textures should be soothing and peaceful
Place clock out of arm’s reach
Comfort items organized neatly near bed
Drink a glass of warm milk
Write problems on paper and leave them there
Stop watching television an hour before bedtime
Massage or cuddle with your loved one
Take a warm bath or shower
Take a sleep aid suggested by doctor
Use a flashlight to use the bathroom
Avoid upsetting activities like bill paying
